  <div class="auction-body">
    <div class="auction-description">
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      Backbone.js, Chai, Mocha, Node.js, and Sails.js
      <p>Currently the GSA Opportunities section of the dashboard is displaying even when there are no open opportunities for GSA. If there are no GSA opportunities, then we don&#39;t want the GSA Opportunities section to show at all.</p>

<p><strong>Scenario: When there are OPEN Agency (GSA) opportunities, user sees Agency (GSA) only opportunities section on the dashboard</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Given I am an authenticated user</li>
<li>And I am a GSA employee</li>
<li>And there are <strong>open</strong> opportunities that are scoped to the GSA
When I go to the dashboard page <a href="https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/dashboard">https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/dashboard</a></li>
<li>Then I should see the three most recent open opportunities in as section labeled &quot;GSA Opportunities&quot;
And I should see a link below that section labeled &quot;See all open GSA opportunities&quot;</li>
<li>And that link should take me to the opportunities page pre-filtered to show <strong>only</strong> opportunities that are open and that are GSA only opportunities</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Scenario: When there are NO OPEN Agency (GSA) opportunities, user DOES NOT see Agency (GSA) only opportunities section on the dashboard</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Given I am an authenticated user</li>
<li>And I am a GSA employee</li>
<li>And there are <strong>no open opportunities</strong> that are scoped to the GSA</li>
<li>When I go to the dashboard page <a href="https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/dashboard">https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/dashboard</a></li>
<li>Then I should NOT see the &quot;GSA Opportunities&quot; section at all</li>
</ul>

<p>As part of this story, we want to make sure the design matches this mock:</p>

<p><img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/100149/19203085/523b420e-8c8a-11e6-971e-cee38155b6b1.png" alt="e038740a-0ba7-11e6-912d-9ab58ebc2ac8"></p>

<h2>General acceptance criteria</h2>

<ul>
<li>Test coverage stays the same or increases</li>
<li>Tests pass</li>
<li><strong>A payment URL is specified in your micro-purchase profile so we can pay the award</strong></li>
</ul>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

